				<div class="brief-text">A large global asset management firm wanted to update and improve their public facing website. Their business was complex and unfortunately that showed through their site. With a maze of unclear product offerings, complex content permissioning, and disparate regional sub-domains, users had a difficult time navigating and finding the information they needed. As the core UX designer on the project, I helped streamline their navigation system, connected their global and regional sites, and worked with designers and developers to create a visual design system that brought clarity to the product experience.</div>
